description:
Bug 38131ajc needs -d option. I am using version 1.1rc1. This is a regression since rc1 and a deviation from javac. I am guessing this may have something to do with a change in the underlying Eclipse compiler.

To reproduce the issue, follow these steps:
1. Create a class in a subpackage:

   package subpackage;

   public class Test {
       public static void main(String[] args) {
           System.out.println("Hello");
       }
   }

2. Compile the class using the following command:

   ajc -d . subpackage\Test.java

Observed Behavior: The command creates a directory "subpackage" within the existing "subpackage" directory.
Expected Behavior: The command should create the directory structure corresponding to the package hierarchy.

This behavior deviates from javac where the command does not create an additional directory.

It would be nice to have the same behavior as javac.
